 :template "main.html"
 :back-to ["The REPL" "index.html"]
 :order 3}
---

The REPL console provides some of the keyboard shortcuts often seen in programs using the Readline library:

@tag[table]{
  @tr{
    @th{Shortcut} @th{Description}
  }
  @tr{
    @td{@code{Tab}} @td{Auto-complete current word.}
  }
  @tr{
    @td{@code{↑} \(Up arrow key)} @td{Previous line in history.}
  }
  @tr{
    @td{@code{↓} \(Down arrow key)} @td{Next line in history.}
  }
  @tr{
    @td{@code{Ctrl + G}} @td{Show documentation for the identifier before the cursor.}
  }
  @tr{
    @td{@code{Ctrl + A}} @td{Move the cursor to the beginning of current line.}
  }
  @tr{
    @td{@code{Ctrl + E}} @td{Move the cursor to the end of current line.}
  }
  @tr{
    @td{@code{Ctrl + F}} @td{Move the cursor one character forward.}
  }
  @tr{
    @td{@code{Ctrl + B}} @td{Move the cursor one character backward.}
  }
  @tr{
    @td{@code{Alt + F}} @td{Move the cursor one word forward.}
  }
  @tr{
    @td{@code{Alt + B}} @td{Move the cursor one word backward.}
  }
  @tr{
    @td{@code{Ctrl + D}} @td{Delete one character at the cursor, or send EOF (exit the REPL) when current line is empty.}
  }
  @tr{
    @td{@code{Ctrl + H}} @td{Delete one character before the cursor.}
  }
  @tr{
    @td{@code{Ctrl + L}} @td{Clear screen.}
  }
}
